title: debug ice: `suggestion must not have overlapping parts` , suggests `-> Box<dyn>`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: A-suggestion-diagnostics
labels.description: Area: suggestions generated by the compiler applied by cargo fix

labels.name: D-invalid-suggestion
labels.description: A structured suggestion resulting in incorrect code

body:
### Code ```Rust type Foo = impl std::fmt::Debug; fn boo2(arg: bool) -> Foo { if arg { "boo2" } else { } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` b2b34bd83192c3d16c88655158f7d8d612513e88 ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0658]: `impl Trait` in type aliases is unstable --> treereduce.out:1:12 | 1 | type Foo = impl std::fmt::Debug; | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ | = note: see issue #63063 for more information = help: add `#![feature(type_alias_impl_trait)]` to the crate attributes to enable error[E0601]: `main` function not found in crate `treereduce` --> treereduce.out:8:2 | 8 | } | ^ consider adding a `main` function to `treereduce.out` error[E0308]: `if` and `else` have incompatible types --> treereduce.out:6:12 | 4 | if arg { | ------ `if` and `else` have incompatible types 5 | "boo2" | ------ expected because of this 6 | } else { | ____________^ 7 | | } | |_____^ expected `&str`, found `()` | help: you could change the return type to be a boxed trait object | 3 | fn boo2(arg: bool) -> Box { | ~~~+~~~ help: if you change the return type to expect trait objects, box the returned expressions | 5 ~ Box::new("boo2") 6 ~ } else Box::new({ 7 ~ }) | ``` The `-> Box` and ``` } else Box::new({}) ``` suggestions are quite interesting :D I suspect the first one causes the debug ice
